    "body": "> @netquery show cli commands how do you use it? probably you set —verbosity flag? Just lower it. Or in your script you initialized logger with trace log level... search `LvlFilterHandler` in your script.\r\n\r\nSorry for the late reply. My current situation is that I have deployed Erigion's RPC Node, and now I want to use Erigon's Golang Client to call this RPC Node. When I was using Erigon's Golang Client, I found that it would output a lot of Trace logs.\r\n\r\nps: The log is not output by Erigon RPC Node. It is generated by Erigon Golang Client when my own program uses Erigon's Golang Client.\r\n\r\nErigon Golang Client: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/devel/rpc/client.go\r\n```\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178083 t=1.433µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178089 t=1.21µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178090 t=1.109µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178092 t=2.63µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178091 t=1.529µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178094 t=1.534µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178093 t=1.175µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178097 t=1.265µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178096 t=1.219µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178098 t=1.34µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.115] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178099 t=1.106µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.116] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178101 t=1.481µs\r\n[TRACE] [11-04|10:07:51.116] Handled RPC response                     reqid=42178095 t=1.267µs\r\n[TRACE] [1